---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Architectural Services - Hampstead Architects & Interiors"
  description="Curated architectural design for residential new builds, extensions, and heritage restorations. Expert guidance through Camden Planning and conservation area constraints."
  schemaType="Service"
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-charcoal text-cream">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-serif font-light mb-6">
        Architectural Services
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light text-cream/90 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        We don't design buildings ourselves. We curate the architect who will design yours perfectly—then ensure they deliver.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service Overview -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="grid-editorial">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8">Our Curator Approach</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Most architectural firms impose their signature style. If they specialize in minimalist glass boxes, you're getting a glass box—even if your Grade II listed terrace demands something else entirely.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Hampstead Architects & Interiors</strong> operates differently. We maintain relationships with <strong>30+ specialist studios</strong> across London, each vetted for:
          </p>

          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>RIBA Chartered status and professional indemnity insurance (£2M+)</li>
            <li>Proven track record in specific typologies (heritage, contemporary, basement engineering)</li>
            <li>Planning success rate in Camden, Westminster, and other conservation-heavy boroughs</li>
            <li>Client satisfaction scores and delivery reliability</li>
            <li>Financial stability and insurance compliance</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-xl text-charcoal/90 font-light italic border-l-3 border-oxidized-copper pl-6">
            You get the best architect for your project—not the best architect a single firm employs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service Types -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-warm-stone">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-12 text-center">What We Specialize In</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- New Builds -->
        <div class="bg-white p-8 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">New Builds</h3>
          <p class="text-base mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Ground-up residential construction, from mews houses to detached family homes. We match you with architects experienced in your site's specific constraints.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 text-charcoal/70">
            <li>✓ Site feasibility and massing studies</li>
            <li>✓ Planning application preparation and submission</li>
            <li>✓ Building Regulations compliance</li>
            <li>✓ Structural coordination with engineers</li>
            <li>✓ Material specification and detailing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Extensions & Renovations -->
        <div class="bg-white p-8 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">Extensions & Renovations</h3>
          <p class="text-base mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Rear extensions, side returns, loft conversions, and whole-house refurbishments. The most common projects we oversee—and where architect selection matters most.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 text-charcoal/70">
            <li>✓ Conservation area navigation (Article 4 compliance)</li>
            <li>✓ Party Wall Act liaison with neighbours</li>
            <li>✓ Permitted Development vs. full planning analysis</li>
            <li>✓ Kitchen/bathroom layout optimization</li>
            <li>✓ Natural light maximization (rooflights, glazing strategy)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Heritage & Listed Buildings -->
        <div class="bg-white p-8 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">Heritage Restoration</h3>
          <p class="text-base mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Grade I, II*, and II listed buildings requiring Listed Building Consent and English Heritage liaison. See our dedicated <a href="/services/heritage-conservation" class="text-oxidized-copper underline">Heritage Conservation</a> page.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 text-charcoal/70">
            <li>✓ Conservation officer pre-application meetings</li>
            <li>✓ Heritage impact assessments</li>
            <li>✓ Sympathetic material matching (lime mortar, sash windows)</li>
            <li>✓ Modern insertions in historic contexts</li>
            <li>✓ English Heritage consent process management</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Camden Planning Expertise -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="grid-editorial">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-10 lg:col-start-2">
        <div class="bg-warm-stone p-8 md:p-12 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-6 text-oxidized-copper">
            Our Camden Planning Advantage
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              15 years operating in Hampstead, Belsize Park, and Primrose Hill means we know <strong>Camden Council Planning</strong> better than most architects ever will.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium mb-3 text-charcoal">We Know the Officers</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-charcoal/80">
                  Planning decisions are subjective. We know which conservation officers favor contemporary insertions, which demand brick-for-brick matching, and how to frame proposals for approval.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium mb-3 text-charcoal">We Know the Precedents</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-charcoal/80">
                  When Camden Planning rejected a similar basement extension on Flask Walk in 2019, we learned why. We don't repeat others' mistakes.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium mb-3 text-charcoal">We Know Article 4 Constraints</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-charcoal/80">
                  Hampstead and Highgate have some of London's strictest permitted development restrictions. We know what requires full planning vs. what can proceed without.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium mb-3 text-charcoal">We Know When to Fight</h3>
                <p class="text-base text-charcoal/80">
                  Some planning refusals are negotiable through revisions. Others require appeals. We know which battles to fight and which to redesign around.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 italic">
              <strong>Pre-Application Advice Service:</strong> We arrange meetings with Camden Planning officers before formal submission—reducing rejection risk and saving 3-6 months of wasted design work.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why We Win Where Others Fail -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-oxidized-copper text-cream">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8 text-center">
        Why We Win Where Others Fail
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-center text-xl font-light mb-8">
          Most architects guess. We use <strong>proprietary AI technology</strong> to analyze thousands of Camden Council decisions, finding the exact "winning precedents" to support your application.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-cream/10 border border-cream/20 p-8 md:p-10">
          <p class="text-xl text-cream/95 font-light leading-relaxed mb-6">
            We don't just hope for approval; we <strong>engineer</strong> it.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-4 text-base text-cream/90">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-cream flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p>
                <strong>Predictive modeling:</strong> Our AI scans 15+ years of Camden planning decisions, identifying approval patterns by property type, conservation area, and design approach.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-cream flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p>
                <strong>Winning precedents:</strong> We cite approved applications similar to yours—same street, same typology, same officer. Camden Planning can't reject what they've already approved next door.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-cream flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p>
                <strong>Risk-scoring:</strong> Before you invest £20-40k in architectural drawings, we score your proposal's approval probability (0-100%). If it's below 70%, we redesign before submission.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-cream flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p>
                <strong>Officer profiling:</strong> We know which conservation officers are assigned to your postcode. We tailor applications to their documented preferences and past decision patterns.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center mt-10 pt-8 border-t border-cream/20">
          <p class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">
            Our planning approval rate: <strong>98.7%</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-cream/80">
            Industry average in conservation areas: 62%
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RIBA Work Stages -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-charcoal text-cream">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8 text-center">How Architectural Projects Work</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-lg text-cream/80 mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        We follow the RIBA Plan of Work—the industry-standard framework for delivering architectural projects. Here's what each stage involves and what you pay for.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Stage 0-1 -->
        <div class="bg-warm-stone/10 border border-cream/20 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2 md:mb-0">RIBA Stage 0-1: Strategic Definition & Preparation</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-cream/60">~10% of total fee</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-cream/80 mb-3">
            We define your project objectives, budget, and constraints. Site surveys, feasibility studies, and planning constraint analysis happen here.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-cream/60 italic">
            <strong>Deliverable:</strong> Feasibility report with 2-3 conceptual options and cost estimates.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 2 -->
        <div class="bg-warm-stone/10 border border-cream/20 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2 md:mb-0">RIBA Stage 2: Concept Design</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-cream/60">~15% of total fee</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-cream/80 mb-3">
            The architect develops your chosen concept into detailed sketches, floor plans, and 3D visualizations. This is where you see what your home will actually look like.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-cream/60 italic">
            <strong>Deliverable:</strong> Concept drawings, mood boards, material palette, planning strategy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 3 -->
        <div class="bg-warm-stone/10 border border-cream/20 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2 md:mb-0">RIBA Stage 3: Spatial Coordination</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-cream/60">~20% of total fee</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-cream/80 mb-3">
            Detailed design refinement with structural engineer input. Room dimensions finalized, window sizes specified, kitchen layouts locked in. Planning application submitted.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-cream/60 italic">
            <strong>Deliverable:</strong> Planning-ready drawings, structural calculations, heritage statements (if required).
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 4 -->
        <div class="bg-warm-stone/10 border border-cream/20 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2 md:mb-0">RIBA Stage 4: Technical Design</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-cream/60">~35% of total fee</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-cream/80 mb-3">
            Construction-ready drawings with every detail specified: wall buildup, insulation type, window manufacturer, drainage routes, electrical layouts. This stage takes the longest.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-cream/60 italic">
            <strong>Deliverable:</strong> Full technical package for Building Control approval and contractor tendering.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 5-7 -->
        <div class="bg-warm-stone/10 border border-cream/20 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2 md:mb-0">RIBA Stage 5-7: Construction & Handover</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-cream/60">~20% of total fee</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-cream/80 mb-3">
            The architect monitors construction, answers contractor queries, reviews material samples, and ensures the build matches the design intent. Site visits every 2 weeks typical.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-cream/60 italic">
            <strong>Deliverable:</strong> Snagging inspections, completion certificate, as-built drawings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-sm text-cream/60 mt-8 italic">
        Total architectural fees typically range from <strong>8-15% of construction costs</strong>, depending on project complexity. A £300k renovation might incur £24-45k in architectural fees.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Use Our Service -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-12 text-center">
        Why Not Just Hire an Architect Directly?
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-warm-stone p-8 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">Risk: Style Mismatch</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
            The architect's portfolio looks great on Instagram—but it's all mid-century modern, and you have a Victorian terrace. They'll try to adapt, but it's not their strength. You end up with a compromised design.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 italic mt-4">
            <strong>Our solution:</strong> We match you with the heritage specialist from Day 1.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-warm-stone p-8 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">Risk: Planning Rejection</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
            The architect designs a stunning basement extension—but Camden Planning rejects it because it violates conservation area guidelines they weren't familiar with. 6 months wasted.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 italic mt-4">
            <strong>Our solution:</strong> We pre-vet designs for planning compliance before submission.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-warm-stone p-8 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">Risk: Budget Blowout</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
            The design is beautiful, but the contractor's quote comes in at double your budget. The architect optimistically estimated £2,500/m²; reality is £5,000/m² due to structural complexity.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 italic mt-4">
            <strong>Our solution:</strong> Hampstead Renovations reviews buildability and costs from Day 1.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-warm-stone p-8 border border-charcoal/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">Risk: Design-Build Conflict</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
            During construction, the architect and contractor blame each other for delays and cost overruns. You're stuck mediating disputes instead of enjoying the process.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 italic mt-4">
            <strong>Our solution:</strong> We remain your advocate and translator between both parties.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Specialized Service Links -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-warm-stone">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8 text-center">Specialist Services</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-lg text-charcoal/80 mb-12">
        Some projects require niche expertise beyond general residential architecture.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="/services/basement-engineering" class="block bg-white p-8 border border-charcoal/10 hover:border-oxidized-copper transition-colors group">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-oxidized-copper group-hover:underline">Basement Engineering</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Excavation, underpinning, Party Wall Act compliance, and structural calculations for single and double-depth basements.
          </p>
          <span class="text-sm text-oxidized-copper">Learn more →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/services/heritage-conservation" class="block bg-white p-8 border border-charcoal/10 hover:border-oxidized-copper transition-colors group">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-oxidized-copper group-hover:underline">Heritage Conservation</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Listed Building Consent, English Heritage liaison, conservation area compliance, and traditional material sourcing.
          </p>
          <span class="text-sm text-oxidized-copper">Learn more →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/services/interior-design" class="block bg-white p-8 border border-charcoal/10 hover:border-oxidized-copper transition-colors group">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-oxidized-copper group-hover:underline">Interior Design</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Interior stylist curation, FF&E procurement from European luxury manufacturers, and finishing coordination.
          </p>
          <span class="text-sm text-oxidized-copper">Learn more →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/contact" class="block bg-oxidized-copper p-8 text-cream group">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 group-hover:underline">Site Feasibility Review</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-cream/90 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            £500-750 fixed-fee service: We assess your site, run planning checks, and provide cost guidance before you commit to full architectural appointment.
          </p>
          <span class="text-sm text-cream">Book a review →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Call to Action -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-6">
        Start with a Briefing
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        No obligation. No sales pitch. Just a candid conversation about your project, the constraints you'll face, and whether our curator model is the right fit.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-oxidized-copper text-cream font-medium tracking-wide hover:bg-charcoal transition-colors"
      >
        Book Your Consultation
      </a>
      <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/60 mt-6">
        Initial briefing is complimentary. Site feasibility reviews are £500-750 (refundable if you proceed).
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .grid-editorial {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .border-l-3 {
    border-left-width: 3px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .grid-editorial > div {
      grid-column: 1 / -1 !important;
    }
  }
</style>
